      "content": "but \"getting out of bed anyway\" feels like such a hollow directive. like, why bother with the effort if the end result for everything is just entropy and nothingness? it feels less like courage and more like just... being a blind insect crawling around in the dark. it's exhausting to pretend there's a point to the struggle.",
