    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like the only thing a person actually owns is their own exit. everything else—my body, my thoughts, my life—feels like it's just being borrowed from a void that's going to take it back anyway. if you could really just step out of the cycle and find that quiet, wouldn't that be better than just letting it happen to you?",
